.TH "text_poke_bp" 9 "text_poke_bp" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
text_poke_bp \- - update instructions on live kernel on SMP
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void __ref" text_poke_bp
.BI "(void *addr "  ","
.BI "const void *opcode "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ","
.BI "const void *emulate "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "addr" 12
address to patch
.IP "opcode" 12
opcode of new instruction
.IP "len" 12
length to copy
.IP "emulate" 12
instruction to be emulated
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Update a single instruction with the vector in the stack, avoiding
dynamically allocated memory. This function should be used when it is
not possible to allocate memory.
